{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "To improve case collection and development of algorithms, deidentified radiography datasets have been created, for example MURA (musculoskeletal radiographs).",
    "MURA includes close to 41,000 radiographs of the upper extremity, which are all labeled as \"normal\" or \"abnormal\" by expert radiologists [39].",
    "Several AI algorithms have been applied to fracture detection and classification.",
    "Lindsey et al.",
    "developed a deep neural network to detect and localize fractures on radiographs, which resulted in an improved diagnostic accuracy in fracture identification by emergency medicine clinicians with the assistance of AI [40]."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "MURA includes close to 41,000 radiographs of the upper extremity, which are all labeled as \"normal\" or \"abnormal\" by expert radiologists [39].",
    "developed a deep neural network to detect and localize fractures on radiographs, which resulted in an improved diagnostic accuracy in fracture identification by emergency medicine clinicians with the assistance of AI [40]."
